      "source": [
        "# 7. PCA para visualización\n",
        "\n",
        "## PCA en dos dimensiones"
      ],
      "id": "907569f7"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "def pca_2d_projection(X):\n",
        "    scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
        "    pca = PCA(n_components=2, random_state=42)\n",
        "\n",
        "    X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)\n",
        "    Z = pca.fit_transform(X_scaled)\n",
        "    return Z, pca"
      ],
      "id": "670ac9a9",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## PCA en tres dimensiones"
      ],
      "id": "cb57d8ea"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "def pca_3d_projection(X):\n",
        "    scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
        "    pca = PCA(n_components=3, random_state=42)\n",
        "\n",
        "    X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)\n",
        "    Z = pca.fit_transform(X_scaled)\n",
        "    return Z, pca"
      ],
      "id": "a08b3050",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# 8. Visualización de separabilidad en 2D"
      ],
      "id": "32d77ed0"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "def plot_pca_2d(Z, y, pca):\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))\n",
        "    for cls in np.unique(y):\n",
        "        idx = y == cls\n",
        "        plt.scatter(Z[idx, 0], Z[idx, 1], label=cls, alpha=0.8)\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(f\"PC1 ({pca.explained_variance_ratio_[0]*100:.2f}% var.)\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(f\"PC2 ({pca.explained_variance_ratio_[1]*100:.2f}% var.)\")\n",
        "    plt.title(\"Proyección PCA en 2D\")\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    plt.grid(True)\n",
        "    plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "c6b83cdc",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Interpretación didáctica:\n",
        "\n",
        "- si las clases forman grupos separados, hay evidencia de separabilidad lineal o casi lineal en el espacio proyectado;\n",
        "- si las clases se traslapan, puede requerirse otra representación o un clasificador más flexible;\n",
        "- si hay outliers, conviene revisar imágenes problemáticas o errores de segmentación/extracción.\n",
        "\n",
        "# 9. Visualización de separabilidad en 3D"
      ],
      "id": "cf0b8fa6"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "def plot_pca_3d(Z, y, pca):\n",
        "    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(9, 7))\n",
        "    ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection=\"3d\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    for cls in np.unique(y):\n",
        "        idx = y == cls\n",
        "        ax.scatter(Z[idx, 0], Z[idx, 1], Z[idx, 2], label=cls, alpha=0.8)\n",
        "\n",
        "    ax.set_xlabel(f\"PC1 ({pca.explained_variance_ratio_[0]*100:.2f}%)\")\n",
        "    ax.set_ylabel(f\"PC2 ({pca.explained_variance_ratio_[1]*100:.2f}%)\")\n",
        "    ax.set_zlabel(f\"PC3 ({pca.explained_variance_ratio_[2]*100:.2f}%)\")\n",
        "    ax.set_title(\"Proyección PCA en 3D\")\n",
        "    ax.legend()\n",
        "    plt.show()"
      ],
